main event: Radar operators at Edwards Air Force Base observed a blinking light moving at a high rate of speed on May 7, 1957.
interesting points: The object accelerated from a point midway across the radar scope and disappeared off the scope in a matter of seconds.
The object was not visible to the naked eye, but only appeared on the radar.
Several witnesses at Edwards AFB reported seeing unidentified objects in the sky on May 7, 1957.
Photographic evidence was submitted, but the images did not clearly depict any distinct objects.
The Air Force investigator concluded that the sighting was likely of a conventional aircraft operating in the local area.
sighted object: blinking light on radar, unidentified aerial objects
photographs: yes, but no clear depictions of objects
